card.description: Investigators have to determine if the officer that fatally shot Patrick Lyoya was reasonably justified in pulling his weapon and firing it based on the circumstances in front of him. The answer would determine whether the unnamed officer that shot and killed Lyoya followed the Grand Rapids Police Department's use of force policy. On Wednesday, Grand Rapids Police Chief Eric Winstrom said he was not commenting on whether his officer’s use of force was in line with the department’s rules.
